      {
        id: 'dict-comprehension', fn: 'Dict comprehension', desc: 'Create a dictionary from an iterable in a single expression.',
        category: 'Data Types', subtitle: '{key: value for item in iterable if condition}',
        signature: '{k: v for k, v in pairs} | {k: fn(k) for k in iterable}',
        descLong: 'Dict comprehensions build a dictionary inline — one key-value pair per iteration. More concise than a for loop with dict[key] = value. Also useful for inverting dicts, filtering, and transforming.',
        code: `# Real-world config processing
raw_config = [
    ("host", "localhost"),
    ("port", "8080"),
    ("debug", "true"),
    ("timeout", "30"),
]
config = {k: v for k, v in raw_config}

# Filter config by key pattern
defaults = {"host": "0.0.0.0", "port": "5000", "debug": "false"}
overrides = {k: v for k, v in config.items() if k in defaults}
# Transform API response to lookup dict
users = [
    {"id": 1, "name": "Alice", "email": "alice@example.com"},
    {"id": 2, "name": "Bob", "email": "bob@example.com"},
users_by_id = {u["id"]: u for u in users}
users_by_email = {u["email"]: u for u in users}
# Invert permission map
permissions = {"read": 1, "write": 2, "execute": 4}
perms_by_value = {v: k for k, v in permissions.items()}
# Filtering with multiple conditions — real data scenario
scores = {"Alice": 92, "Bob": 65, "Carol": 88, "David": 55}
honors = {name: score for name, score in scores.items()
          if score >= 80 and name[0].isupper()}
# Type conversion — real config loading
env_vars = {"PORT": "8080", "WORKERS": "4", "DEBUG": "false"}
config_dict = {
    "port": int(env_vars.get("PORT", 5000)),
    "workers": int(env_vars.get("WORKERS", 2)),
    "debug": env_vars.get("DEBUG", "false").lower() == "true",
}`,
        tips: [
          'Dict comprehension is O(n) like a loop — syntactically cleaner for simple key-value constructions',
          'Inverting a dict: `{v: k for k, v in d.items()}` — only works if values are unique/hashable',
